WELCOME
East and West blend
brilliantly on today's menu,
with an eclectic array of food
created by United Airlines'
Executive Chef Kanji Sato and
his team in Narita, working in
partnership with United's
Corporate Chef Eric Kopelow.
Nagano-born Chef Sato began
his culinary career at the
Prince Hotels in Yokohama,
Montreal and Toronto prior to
joining United in Japan. He
designed the expanded Obento
offered on selected flights.
Chef Sato received the Five
Star Diamond Award as one of
the World's Best Chefs in
1999 from The American
Academy of Hospitality
Sciences.
Chef Kopelow, a graduate of
New York's famed Culinary
Institute of America, has been
awarded over 30 gold, silver
and bronze medals from
culinary competitions around
the world. Most recently, he
was inducted into both CIA's
Hall of Fame and the 2000-
2001 Lexington's Who's Who
Registry of Executives and
Professionals.
Please enjoy these dishes on
today's flight.
